content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Osmumten

Osmumten was the last pharaoh of the line of pharaohs chosen by Tumeken, the God of the Sun. Besides being ruler, Osmumten was a passionate hunter, wielding his specially designed weapon, he adventured across the land, fighting the greatest beasts. Osmumten was the pharaoh somewhere around the Second Age, when the present-day Kharidian Desert was invaded by a powerful invader.

Osmumten was fighting on the frontline in the war, which ended when Tumeken sacrificed himself to stop the invading forces. Following Tumeken's supposed death, his widow Elidinis, the Goddess of Fertility, gave Osmumten Tumeken's heka and the Elidinis' ward before retreating to mourn her husband's death and the unfortunate fate of her daughter Amascut.

Osmumten would continue ruling as the last pharaoh appointed by Tumeken. The exact details of Osmumten's death is unknown, but the royal line ended with him.

{{external|rs}}
'''Osmumten''' was the last pharaoh of the line of pharaohs chosen by [[Tumeken]], the God of the Sun. Besides being ruler, Osmumten was a passionate hunter, wielding his [[Osmumten's fang|specially designed weapon]], he adventured across the land, fighting the greatest beasts. Osmumten was the pharaoh somewhere around the [[Second Age]], when the present-day [[Kharidian Desert]] was invaded by a powerful invader. 

Osmumten was fighting on the frontline in the war, which ended when Tumeken sacrificed himself to stop the invading forces. 
Following Tumeken's supposed death, his widow [[Elidinis]], the Goddess of Fertility, gave Osmumten [[Tumeken's heka]] and the [[Elidinis' ward]] before retreating to mourn her husband's death and the unfortunate fate of her daughter [[Amascut]].

Osmumten would continue ruling as the last pharaoh appointed by Tumeken. The exact details of Osmumten's death is unknown, but the royal line ended with him.
